/etc - contains repository and package manager configuration files
important files :
/etc/yum.repos.d/ --> repository definitions (RHEl/CentOS)
/etc/dnf/dnf.conf
/etc/apt/sources.list(Ubuntu/debian)

/var -> Important during patching
Key subdirectories
/var/cache -> downloaded packages stored temporarily
/var/lib/rpm -> rpm database (  The RPM database is a local database on RPM-based Linux systems (Redhat, CentOS, AlmaLinux) that stores information about packages managed by RPM package manager)
/var/lib/dnf or /var/lib/yum - package metadata
/var/logs - patching logs
if /var is full updates fail

/usr -> Installed packages and binaries are updated here during patching
/boot -> Important when kernel patching
/tmp -> /tmp used for temporary extraction of packages during updates
